          "date": "2019-02-26 14:51:54.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-11931 lnd: relax throttling limit",
        "message": "LU-11931 lnd: relax throttling limit\n\nOn large system it is better to allow head room for outstanding\ntransmits beyond the negotiated queue depth. It appears that this\nrestriction causes RDMA timeout, since tx stay on the tx_queue\nfor a long period of time.\n\nPreviously, there was concurrent_sends module parameter which\ncould be set to a maximum of queue_depth * 2. With the removal\nof concurrent_sends, simply have a ceiling of queue_depth * 2\nconcurrent sends.\n\nSigned-off-by: Amir Shehata <ashehata@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: Ide04a656553964d9013f91ba5ad3fd81bbe84a67\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
